(3, 'Papaya', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong></big> Pepaya<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Carica papaya</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong></big> Caricaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong></big> Amerika Tengah dan Selatan</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nPepaya adalah tanaman buah tropis yang dikenal karena buahnya yang manis, dagingnya yang lembut, dan kandungan nutrisinya yang tinggi. Selain buahnya, daun dan bijinya juga sering dimanfaatkan untuk pengobatan tradisional.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Pohon:</strong> Tumbuh tegak hingga 3&ndash;10 meter, batang berongga dan tidak bercabang.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Besar, berbentuk menjari, dan tumbuh di bagian atas pohon.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Buah:</strong> Berbentuk lonjong atau bulat, kulit hijau saat muda dan kuning/oranye saat matang.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daging buah:</strong> Lembut, berwarna oranye kemerahan, manis, dan berair.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Biji:</strong> Hitam, bundar, dilapisi gel.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dikonsumsi langsung sebagai buah segar.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Diolah menjadi jus, salad, manisan, atau bahan masakan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Daun pepaya digunakan sebagai pelunak daging dan pengobatan alami.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kaya akan vitamin C, A, serat, dan enzim papain yang baik untuk pencernaan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tumbuh optimal di daerah tropis dengan sinar matahari penuh.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membutuhkan tanah subur dan drainase baik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tidak tahan genangan air.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dapat mulai berbuah sekitar 6&ndash;9 bulan setelah tanam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong> </big>Papaya<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> </big><em>Carica papaya</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong></big> Caricaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> Central and South America</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nPapaya is a tropical fruit tree known for its sweet, juicy flesh and high nutritional value. Aside from the fruit, its leaves and seeds are also traditionally used for medicinal purposes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Tree:</strong> Grows upright up to 3&ndash;10 meters, with a hollow, unbranched trunk.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Large, palm-shaped, growing at the top of the stem.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Fruit:</strong> Oval or round, green when young and yellow/orange when ripe.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Flesh:</strong> Soft, reddish-orange, sweet, and juicy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Seeds:</strong> Small, round, black, and coated in a gelatinous layer.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consumed fresh or made into juice, salad, preserves, or cooking ingredients.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Leaves are used as a meat tenderizer and in traditional medicine.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rich in vitamin C, A, fiber, and papain enzyme that aids digestion.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Tips:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thrives in tropical climates with full sun exposure.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Requires fertile, well-drained soil.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sensitive to waterlogging.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Can begin to bear fruit within 6&ndash;9 months after planting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Sayur', '6847d74d240bb.jpg', '68217215b11d7.png'),
(4, 'Luttuce', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong></big> Selada<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong> </big><em>Lactuca sativa</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong></big> Asteraceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong> </big>Timur Tengah dan Mediterania</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nSelada adalah tanaman sayuran daun yang sering digunakan sebagai bahan utama salad, pelengkap sandwich, dan hiasan makanan. Selada terkenal karena teksturnya yang renyah dan rasa yang segar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Berwarna hijau muda hingga hijau tua atau kemerahan, lembut atau keriting tergantung varietasnya.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang:</strong> Pendek, tumbuh membentuk roset.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Akar:</strong> Serabut, dangkal.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Rasa:</strong> Segar, sedikit manis atau hambar, tergantung jenis.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Jenis Populer:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Selada keriting (<em>leaf lettuce</em>)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Selada kepala (<em>butterhead / iceberg</em>)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Selada romaine</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Selada merah</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bahan utama salad dan sandwich.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kaya akan vitamin A, K, folat, dan antioksidan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membantu hidrasi tubuh karena kandungan air yang tinggi.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tumbuh optimal di daerah sejuk, dengan suhu 15&ndash;25&deg;C.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tanah subur, gembur, dan lembap, tapi tidak becek.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Perlu penyiraman rutin dan tempat teduh pada siang terik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Panen bisa dilakukan 30&ndash;45 hari setelah tanam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong></big> Lettuce<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong></big> <em>Lactuca sativa</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong></big> Asteraceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> Middle East and Mediterranean region</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nLettuce is a leafy vegetable commonly used in salads, sandwiches, and as garnish. It is appreciated for its crisp texture and refreshing taste.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Vary from light green to dark green or reddish, either soft or curly depending on the type.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Stem:</strong> Short, forming a rosette.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Roots:</strong> Fibrous and shallow.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Flavor:</strong> Mild and fresh, slightly sweet or neutral.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Popular Varieties:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Leaf lettuce</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Butterhead or iceberg lettuce</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Romaine lettuce</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Red lettuce</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Widely used in salads, sandwiches, and wraps.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rich in vitamin A, K, folate, and antioxidants.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hydrating due to its high water content.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Tips:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prefers cool climates (15&ndash;25&deg;C).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Needs fertile, loose, and moist soil with good drainage.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Requires regular watering and partial shade during hot days.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ready to harvest in 30&ndash;45 days after planting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Sayur', '6847dd55a8a14.jpg', '68217aff1b08a.png'),
(6, 'Ginger', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong></big> Jahe<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Zingiber officinale</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong></big> Zingiberaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong></big> Asia Tenggara</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nJahe adalah tanaman herbal yang banyak digunakan sebagai rempah, obat tradisional, dan minuman penghangat tubuh. Rimpangnya yang harum dan pedas menjadi bahan penting dalam kuliner Asia maupun pengobatan alami.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Rimpang (akar):</strong> Tebal, bercabang, berwarna cokelat keemasan di luar dan kuning pucat di dalam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang semu:</strong> Hijau, tegak, menyerupai batang rumput.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Panjang, ramping, dan tersusun berseling.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Bunga:</strong> Tumbuh dari rimpang, berwarna hijau kekuningan dengan sedikit ungu, jarang muncul jika ditanam untuk panen rimpangnya.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bumbu dapur untuk menambah aroma dan rasa hangat.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Minuman herbal seperti wedang jahe dan teh jahe.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Obat alami untuk masuk angin, mual, radang tenggorokan, dan meningkatkan kekebalan tubuh.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mengandung gingerol, zat aktif dengan sifat antiinflamasi dan antioksidan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cocok ditanam di daerah tropis atau subtropis dengan curah hujan cukup.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tanah gembur, lembap, dan kaya humus adalah media ideal.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Penyiraman teratur tetapi tidak becek.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dapat dipanen setelah 8&ndash;10 bulan setelah tanam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong></big> Ginger<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong></big> <em>Zingiber officinale</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong></big> Zingiberaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> Southeast Asia</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nGinger is a tropical herb known for its aromatic and spicy rhizomes. Widely used in culinary, traditional medicine, and warm beverages, it has become a global favorite due to its flavor and health benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Rhizome:</strong> Thick, branched, light brown on the outside with pale yellow flesh inside.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Pseudostem:</strong> Upright, green, grass-like in appearance.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Narrow, elongated, arranged alternately.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Flowers:</strong> Rarely appear; yellowish-green with purple tips, sprouting from the rhizome base.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Culinary spice to enhance flavor and warmth in food.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Key ingredient in herbal drinks like ginger tea and traditional infusions.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Natural remedy for nausea, colds, sore throat, and immune support.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Contains gingerol, a compound with anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Tips:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Grows well in warm, humid climates with moderate rainfall.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prefers loose, fertile, and well-draining soil rich in organic matter.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Needs consistent moisture but avoid waterlogging.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ready for harvest 8&ndash;10 months after planting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Musiman', '6847dbcce8de6.jpg', '68217b3be74b1.png'),
(7, 'Cauliflower', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong></big> Kol Bunga<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Brassica oleracea</em> var. <em>botrytis</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong></big> Brassicaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong></big> Laut Tengah</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong><br />\r\nKol bunga adalah sayuran berbunga yang menyerupai brokoli, tetapi dengan warna putih gading. Rasanya lembut dan sedikit manis, sangat cocok untuk berbagai masakan sehat. Sayuran ini kaya akan vitamin dan rendah kalori, menjadikannya pilihan populer dalam pola makan sehat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Kepala bunga:</strong> Padat, berwarna putih hingga krem, tersusun dari kuntum bunga yang rapat.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Lebar dan berwarna hijau pucat hingga biru kehijauan, melindungi kepala bunga.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang:</strong> Pendek dan kuat.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Ukuran:</strong> Kepala bunga dapat tumbuh hingga diameter 15&ndash;25 cm.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Diolah menjadi sup, tumis, kari, panggang, atau nasi kol bunga (pengganti nasi).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kaya vitamin C, vitamin B6, serat, dan antioksidan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membantu menurunkan berat badan dan menjaga kesehatan sistem pencernaan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Baik untuk diet keto atau rendah karbohidrat.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tumbuh optimal di daerah beriklim sejuk (15&ndash;20&deg;C).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membutuhkan sinar matahari penuh dan tanah yang subur serta memiliki drainase baik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Penyiraman rutin dan menjaga agar kepala bunga tidak terkena sinar matahari langsung (bisa dibungkus daun).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Panen dilakukan saat kepala bunga padat dan belum mekar.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong></big> Cauliflower<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> </big><em>Brassica oleracea</em> var. <em>botrytis</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong> </big>Brassicaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> Mediterranean region</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nCauliflower is a flowering vegetable similar to broccoli but typically white or creamy in color. It has a mild, slightly sweet flavor and is favored in healthy diets due to its high nutritional value and low calories.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Head:</strong> Compact, white to ivory-colored curds made up of tight flower clusters.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Broad, pale green to bluish-green, often wrap around the head for protection.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Stem:</strong> Short and sturdy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Size:</strong> Heads can grow up to 15&ndash;25 cm in diameter.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Commonly used in soups, stir-fries, curries, roasting, or made into cauliflower rice.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rich in vitamin C, B6, fiber, and antioxidants.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Promotes weight loss and supports digestive health.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Popular in keto and low-carb diets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Tips:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Grows best in cool climates (15&ndash;20&deg;C).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Needs full sunlight and fertile, well-drained soil.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Water regularly and shield the head from direct sun by wrapping with its own leaves.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Harvest when the head is firm and fully formed but before it starts to flower.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Sayur', '68467688d8a7d.jpg', '68217b5628eda.png'),
(8, 'Broccoli', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong> </big>Brokoli<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Brassica oleracea</em> var. <em>italica</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong></big> Brassicaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong> </big>Laut Tengah (wilayah selatan Italia)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nBrokoli adalah sayuran berbunga yang sangat bergizi dan digemari dalam berbagai olahan makanan. Memiliki rasa khas yang sedikit pahit, brokoli dikenal sebagai &ldquo;superfood&rdquo; karena kandungan antioksidan dan vitaminnya yang tinggi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Bagian dimakan:</strong> Kuntum bunga berwarna hijau tua atau kehijauan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang:</strong> Tegak dan kokoh.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Besar, hijau kebiruan, dan tumbuh mengelilingi batang utama.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Akar:</strong> Tunggang pendek.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Masa panen:</strong> 60&ndash;90 hari setelah tanam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dikonsumsi dalam bentuk kukus, tumis, rebus, atau sebagai salad.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mengandung vitamin C, vitamin K, zat besi, kalsium, dan serat.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Baik untuk kesehatan jantung, tulang, dan pencernaan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dikenal membantu mencegah peradangan dan mendukung sistem kekebalan tubuh.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tumbuh optimal di dataran tinggi dengan suhu sejuk (15&ndash;25&deg;C).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Butuh tanah yang subur, gembur, dan kaya bahan organik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Penyiraman rutin tetapi tidak berlebihan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hindari genangan air dan jaga dari hama ulat dan kutu daun.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong></big> Broccoli<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong></big> <em>Brassica oleracea</em> var. <em>italica</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong></big> Brassicaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> Mediterranean (Southern Italy)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nBroccoli is a nutrient-rich flowering vegetable known for its health benefits and versatility in cooking. Slightly bitter in taste, it is considered a &ldquo;superfood&rdquo; due to its powerful antioxidants and vitamin content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Edible Part:</strong> Dense clusters of green flower buds.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Stem:</strong> Upright and firm.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Large, bluish-green, growing around the central stalk.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Roots:</strong> Short taproot.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Harvest Time:</strong> 60&ndash;90 days after planting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Commonly steamed, stir-fried, boiled, or served raw in salads.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>High in vitamin C, vitamin K, fiber, calcium, and iron.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Supports heart health, digestion, and bone strength.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Known to reduce inflammation and enhance immune function.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Tips:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thrives in cooler climates, best grown at 15&ndash;25&deg;C.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Requires fertile, well-drained soil rich in organic matter.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Regular watering, but avoid waterlogging.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Protect from pests like caterpillars and aphids.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Sayur', '6847d58ef3647.jpg', '68218bab2c496.png'),
(9, 'Green Mustard', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong> </big>Sawi Hijau<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Brassica rapa</em> subsp. <em>chinensis</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong></big> Brassicaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong> </big>Asia Timur (Tiongkok dan sekitarnya)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nSawi hijau adalah sayuran daun yang populer di Indonesia dan berbagai negara Asia. Tanaman ini tumbuh cepat, mudah dibudidayakan, dan sering digunakan dalam masakan seperti tumisan, sup, mie, hingga lalapan segar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Berwarna hijau cerah, lebar, dan memanjang dengan tekstur renyah.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang:</strong> Putih kehijauan, tebal, dan lunak.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Akar:</strong> Serabut pendek.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Pertumbuhan:</strong> Dapat dipanen dalam 30&ndash;45 hari setelah tanam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Digunakan dalam berbagai masakan tradisional dan modern.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mengandung vitamin A, C, K, asam folat, dan serat tinggi.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Baik untuk pencernaan dan meningkatkan sistem kekebalan tubuh.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dapat tumbuh di dataran rendah maupun tinggi.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ideal ditanam di tanah gembur, lembap, dan kaya bahan organik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membutuhkan sinar matahari penuh atau teduh parsial.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Penyiraman rutin dan pemupukan organik ringan disarankan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong></big> Green Mustard / Pak Choy<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> </big><em>Brassica rapa</em> subsp. <em>chinensis</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong></big> Brassicaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> East Asia (primarily China)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nGreen mustard is a fast-growing leafy vegetable widely used in Asian cuisine. Known for its tender stalks and vibrant green leaves, it is popular in stir-fries, soups, noodles, and fresh salads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Bright green, broad, and crunchy in texture.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Stems:</strong> Pale green, juicy, and soft.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Roots:</strong> Shallow fibrous roots.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Growth Cycle:</strong> Ready to harvest in 30&ndash;45 days after planting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Common in traditional dishes and modern culinary creations.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rich in vitamins A, C, K, folate, and dietary fiber.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Supports digestion and boosts immunity.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Tips:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Can grow in lowland or highland areas.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prefers loose, moist, nutrient-rich soil.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thrives under full sun or partial shade.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Water regularly and apply organic fertilizer for best yield.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Sayur', '6847d23e4d7d2.png', '682193ab677e8.png'),
(10, 'Coffee Tree', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong></big> Tanaman Kopi<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong> </big><em>Coffea spp.</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong> </big>Rubiaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong></big> Afrika Sub-Sahara (terutama Ethiopia)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nTanaman kopi adalah semak atau pohon kecil yang dibudidayakan secara luas di berbagai belahan dunia tropis untuk menghasilkan biji kopi&mdash;komoditas penting yang menjadi bahan dasar salah satu minuman paling populer di dunia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang:</strong> Berkayu, bercabang banyak, tinggi 2&ndash;5 meter (tergantung jenis dan pemangkasan).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Mengilap, hijau gelap, berbentuk lonjong, tersusun berlawanan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Bunga:</strong> Kecil, putih, harum, mekar berkelompok di ketiak daun.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Buah (Ceri Kopi):</strong> Bulat kecil, berwarna hijau saat muda, berubah menjadi merah saat matang, berisi 2 biji kopi.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Jenis Umum:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><em>Arabica</em> &ndash; Rasa halus dan asam ringan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><em>Robusta</em> &ndash; Lebih kuat, pahit, dan tinggi kafein.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Biji kopi diolah menjadi minuman, bubuk, atau kopi instan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Daun kopi bisa diolah menjadi teh herbal.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ampas kopi digunakan sebagai pupuk organik dan scrub alami.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tumbuh optimal di dataran tinggi (800&ndash;2.000 mdpl) dengan suhu 15&ndash;24&deg;C.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membutuhkan naungan sebagian dan curah hujan merata sepanjang tahun.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tanah ideal: subur, berdrainase baik, pH 5.5&ndash;6.5.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pemangkasan rutin dan pemupukan organik meningkatkan hasil panen.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong></big> Coffee Plant<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> </big><em>Coffea spp.</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong></big> Rubiaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> Sub-Saharan Africa (primarily Ethiopia)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nThe coffee plant is a small tree or shrub cultivated around the world&rsquo;s tropical zones for its valuable beans. These beans are roasted and brewed into one of the world&rsquo;s most beloved beverages&mdash;coffee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Trunk:</strong> Woody with many branches, typically 2&ndash;5 meters tall.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Glossy, dark green, oval-shaped, arranged oppositely.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Flowers:</strong> Small, white, fragrant blossoms that cluster along leaf axils.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Fruit (Coffee Cherry):</strong> Small round fruits that ripen from green to red, containing two coffee beans.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Popular Varieties:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><em>Arabica</em> &ndash; Smooth, mild acidity, and nuanced flavor.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><em>Robusta</em> &ndash; Strong, bitter, and higher in caffeine.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Coffee beans are processed into brewed drinks, instant coffee, or ground powder.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Young leaves may be used for herbal tea.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Coffee grounds are repurposed as fertilizer and natural body scrubs.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Tips:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thrives at high altitudes (800&ndash;2,000 meters) with temperatures between 15&ndash;24&deg;C.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prefers partial shade and consistent rainfall.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Grows best in fertile, well-drained soils with pH 5.5&ndash;6.5.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pruning and organic composting improve both growth and yield.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Tahunan', '683d7addc4883.jpg', '682193beacd98.png'),
(11, 'Coconut Tree', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong> </big>Pohon Kelapa<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Cocos nucifera</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong> </big>Arecaceae (Palmae)<br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong></big> Wilayah pesisir tropis Asia Tenggara dan Pasifik</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nPohon kelapa adalah salah satu tanaman paling ikonik di wilayah tropis. Selain menghasilkan buah yang bergizi dan serbaguna, kelapa juga memiliki nilai ekonomi, budaya, dan ekologis yang tinggi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang:</strong> Tinggi, ramping, dan tidak bercabang, dapat tumbuh hingga 30 meter.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Menjari panjang dan melengkung, dengan panjang daun mencapai 4&ndash;6 meter.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Buah:</strong> Berbentuk bulat lonjong dengan sabut tebal, daging putih, dan air kelapa segar di dalamnya.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Akar:</strong> Berserabut dan menyebar luas, membantu pohon bertahan di berbagai kondisi tanah.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Buahnya digunakan untuk minuman, makanan, dan bahan baku minyak kelapa.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Daunnya dimanfaatkan untuk atap tradisional, kerajinan tangan, dan upacara adat.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Batangnya bisa dipakai sebagai bahan bangunan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tempurung dan sabut kelapa digunakan untuk bahan bakar, pupuk, dan kerajinan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membutuhkan sinar matahari penuh dan iklim tropis hangat.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tumbuh optimal di tanah berpasir atau lempung yang memiliki drainase baik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Penyiraman tambahan dibutuhkan saat musim kemarau.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bisa tumbuh di daerah pantai hingga dataran rendah.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong> </big>Coconut Tree<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> </big><em>Cocos nucifera</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong> </big>Arecaceae (Palms)<br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong> </big>Coastal tropical regions of Southeast Asia and the Pacific</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nThe coconut tree is a tropical icon known for its versatility and economic value. From its refreshing water to its durable wood and beautiful fronds, every part of this tree serves a purpose.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Trunk:</strong> Tall, slender, and unbranched; can grow up to 30 meters.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Long and feather-like, arching up to 4&ndash;6 meters.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Fruit:</strong> Oval-shaped with a fibrous husk, white edible flesh, and refreshing coconut water inside.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Roots:</strong> Fibrous and wide-spreading, helping it survive various soil conditions.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Coconuts are used for drinks, cooking, oil production, and desserts.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Leaves are woven into roofs, mats, and ceremonial decorations.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Trunk is used for building materials and furniture.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Husks and shells are repurposed for crafts, fuel, and organic fertilizers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Tips:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Requires full sun and a warm tropical climate.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thrives in sandy or loamy soils with good drainage.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Extra watering may be needed during dry seasons.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ideal for coastal areas and lowland tropical zones.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Tahunan', '684b6f5e6f074.jpeg', '682193d6aba16.png'),
(12, 'Pine Tree', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong></big> Pohon Cemara<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Casuarina equisetifolia</em> (untuk cemara laut, bisa disesuaikan dengan jenis spesifiknya)<br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong> </big>Casuarinaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong> </big>Asia Tenggara dan wilayah pesisir tropis</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nPohon cemara adalah tanaman evergreen yang dikenal karena daunnya yang runcing menyerupai jarum dan bentuknya yang menjulang tinggi. Selain memberikan kesan sejuk dan tenang, pohon ini juga sering digunakan sebagai penahan angin di daerah pantai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang:</strong> Tinggi, lurus, dan berkayu kuat. Bisa tumbuh hingga lebih dari 20 meter.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Tipis seperti jarum, tersusun spiral, dan selalu hijau sepanjang tahun.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Buah:</strong> Kecil, berbentuk kerucut, mirip runjung pada pohon pinus.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Akar:</strong> Dalam dan kuat, sangat baik untuk mencegah erosi tanah.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cocok sebagai tanaman peneduh, penghias taman, dan pelindung angin di area terbuka.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kayunya digunakan untuk bahan bangunan, kayu bakar, dan kerajinan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Memiliki nilai estetika tinggi sebagai tanaman hias lanskap.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tumbuh baik di daerah terbuka dengan sinar matahari penuh.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tahan terhadap kekeringan dan angin kencang.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tidak memerlukan banyak perawatan, cukup penyiraman rutin di awal masa tanam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dapat tumbuh di berbagai jenis tanah, termasuk tanah pasir.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong></big> Casuarina Tree / Australian Pine<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong></big> <em>Casuarina equisetifolia</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong></big> Casuarinaceae<br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> Southeast Asia and tropical coastal areas</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nCasuarina trees are evergreen conifers known for their tall, slender appearance and needle-like foliage. Often planted along coastlines or in open spaces, they offer beauty, shade, and protection against wind erosion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Trunk:</strong> Tall, straight, and woody; can grow over 20 meters.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Thin, needle-shaped, arranged in spirals, and stay green year-round.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Fruit:</strong> Small, cone-like structures resembling pinecones.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Roots:</strong> Deep and strong, ideal for preventing soil erosion.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Popular as windbreaks, shade providers, and ornamental trees in landscaping.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Timber is useful for construction, firewood, and traditional crafts.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Adds an elegant, calming touch to gardens and public areas.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Tips:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thrives in open areas with full sun exposure.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Drought and wind resistant.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Low maintenance; regular watering is needed only during early growth.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Adaptable to various soil types, including sandy soils.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Musiman', '6846760413efe.jpg', '682193f467a6e.png'),
(13, 'Bougainvillea', '<p><big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong> </big><em>Bougainvillea spp.</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal Tanaman:</strong></big> Amerika Selatan (terutama Brasil, Peru, dan Argentina)<br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong></big> Nyctaginaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nBougainvillea adalah tanaman hias merambat atau semak yang dikenal karena keindahan brakteanya yang berwarna cerah. Tanaman ini tumbuh cepat, mudah dibentuk, dan dapat berbunga hampir sepanjang tahun di daerah tropis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Daunnya berwarna hijau dan berbentuk lonjong.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Braktea (daun pelindung bunga) hadir dalam berbagai warna seperti ungu, merah, pink, kuning, oranye, atau putih.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bunga sejati kecil, berwarna putih atau kuning pucat, terletak di tengah braktea.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Batangnya berkayu dan sering kali berduri.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sebagai penghias taman, pagar, dinding, atau pergola.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bisa dijadikan bonsai atau tanaman pot gantung.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membantu mencegah erosi tanah di lereng.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membutuhkan sinar matahari penuh untuk berbunga optimal.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tanah harus memiliki drainase yang baik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tahan terhadap kekeringan, tidak perlu sering disiram.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong></big> <em>Bougainvillea spp.</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> South America (notably Brazil, Peru, and Argentina)<br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong> </big>Nyctaginaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nBougainvillea is a fast-growing ornamental vine or shrub, admired for its colorful bracts that resemble flowers. It thrives in warm climates and blooms almost year-round.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Leaves are green, oval-shaped, and alternately arranged.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bracts come in bright colors such as purple, red, pink, yellow, orange, or white.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The true flowers are small, tubular, and pale in color.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Stems are woody and often thorny.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Great for decorating gardens, fences, walls, and pergolas.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Can be shaped into bonsai or grown in hanging pots.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Helps reduce soil erosion on slopes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Requires full sunlight for best blooming.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Needs well-drained soil.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Drought-tolerant; does not require frequent watering.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Hias', '684675b7e18fd.jpg', '68219409562ab.png'),
(16, 'Avocado', '<p><big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Persea americana</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal Tanaman:</strong> </big>Meksiko dan Amerika Tengah<br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong></big> Lauraceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nAlpukat adalah pohon buah tropis yang populer karena daging buahnya yang lembut dan kaya nutrisi. Cocok ditanam di berbagai wilayah Indonesia, tanaman ini juga memiliki nilai ekonomis tinggi dan manfaat kesehatan yang luar biasa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang:</strong> Pohon berukuran sedang (15&ndash;20 meter), bercabang lebar.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Hijau mengilap, berbentuk lonjong, tersusun spiral di ujung ranting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Bunga:</strong> Kecil, berwarna hijau kekuningan, muncul dalam kelompok.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Buah:</strong> Beragam bentuk (bulat, pir, oval), kulit hijau atau ungu kehitaman saat matang, dengan satu biji besar di tengah.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kandungan Nutrisi:</strong></big><br />\r\nMengandung lemak tak jenuh tunggal, vitamin E, K, C, B6, kalium, serat, dan antioksidan yang baik untuk kesehatan jantung dan kulit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dikonsumsi langsung, dijadikan jus, salad, atau guacamole.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bermanfaat untuk menjaga berat badan, menurunkan kolesterol, dan menunjang kesehatan otak serta jantung.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tanah harus gembur, kaya bahan organik, dan memiliki drainase baik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tumbuh optimal di ketinggian 200&ndash;1.000 mdpl.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sinar matahari penuh dan penyiraman cukup sangat penting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pemupukan organik dan penyiangan rutin membantu mempercepat pertumbuhan dan pembungaan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> </big><em>Persea americana</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong> </big>Mexico and Central America<br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong></big> Lauraceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Overview:</strong></big><br />\r\nAvocado is a tropical fruit tree highly valued for its creamy texture and rich nutritional content. It thrives in many regions of Indonesia and plays an important role both economically and nutritionally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Trunk:</strong> Medium-sized tree (15&ndash;20 meters) with a wide canopy.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Glossy green, elliptical, arranged spirally at branch tips.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Flowers:</strong> Small, greenish-yellow, clustered blooms.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Fruit:</strong> Varies in shape (pear, round, oval), skin turns green to dark purple when ripe, with a large central seed.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Nutritional Value:</strong></big><br />\r\nRich in monounsaturated fats, vitamin E, K, C, B6, fiber, potassium, and antioxidants &mdash; supporting heart, brain, and skin health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consumed fresh, or made into juice, salad, or guacamole.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Helps with weight management, lowers cholesterol, and promotes overall wellness.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Tips:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Prefers fertile, well-drained soil rich in organic matter.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Grows best at 200&ndash;1,000 meters above sea level.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Needs full sunlight and regular watering.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Organic fertilizer and routine weeding enhance growth and flowering.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Buah', '6848f854c6cb1.jpeg', '6847d99c33499.png'),
(17, 'Pineapple', '<p><big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Ananas comosus</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong></big> Amerika Selatan (terutama Brasil dan Paraguay)<br />\r\n<strong><big>Famili:</big></strong><big> </big>Bromeliaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nNanas adalah tanaman tropis yang terkenal dengan buahnya yang manis, segar, dan kaya akan vitamin C. Tanaman ini tumbuh rendah di permukaan tanah dengan daun tajam membentuk roset. Buah nanas tumbuh dari tengah roset dan memiliki kulit bersisik serta mahkota daun di atasnya.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Panjang, kaku, tebal, dengan tepi berduri, berwarna hijau keabu-abuan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Buah:</strong> Berwarna kuning keemasan saat matang, dagingnya lembut, manis, dan sedikit asam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Akar:</strong> Dangkal, menyebar di permukaan tanah.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dikonsumsi langsung atau diolah menjadi jus, selai, atau bahan campuran masakan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mengandung bromelain yang bermanfaat untuk pencernaan dan antiinflamasi.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Digunakan dalam industri makanan, minuman, bahkan kosmetik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tumbuh baik di tanah gembur dengan drainase baik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membutuhkan sinar matahari penuh.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pemupukan rutin penting, terutama pupuk kandang dan kalium.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Masa panen sekitar 12&ndash;18 bulan setelah tanam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> </big><em>Ananas comosus</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> South America (mainly Brazil and Paraguay)<br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong> </big>Bromeliaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>General Description:</strong></big><br />\r\nPineapple is a tropical plant known for its sweet, juicy fruit rich in vitamin C. It grows low to the ground with long, spiky leaves forming a rosette. The fruit emerges from the center, featuring a spiny outer skin and a leafy crown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Long, stiff, thick, with spiny edges; grayish-green in color.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Fruit:</strong> Golden yellow when ripe, soft textured, sweet with a slight tang.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Roots:</strong> Shallow and spread along the soil surface.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Eaten fresh or processed into juice, jam, or culinary ingredients.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Contains bromelain, beneficial for digestion and anti-inflammatory effects.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Used in food, beverage, and cosmetic industries.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Instructions:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thrives in well-drained, loose soil.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Requires full sunlight exposure.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Regular fertilization, especially with compost and potassium-rich fertilizers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Harvest time is around 12&ndash;18 months after planting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Buah', '684d0765646ab.jpg', '684d0765cf308.png');
INSERT INTO `tanaman` (`id`, `nama`, `deskripsi`, `nama_latin`, `famili`, `asal`, `manfaat`, `cara_menanam`, `deskripsi_en`, `link_referensi`, `video_youtube`, `link_deskripsi_en`, `kategori`, `gambar`, `qrcode`) VALUES
(18, 'Passion Fruit', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong></big> Markisa<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong> </big><em>Passiflora edulis</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong> </big>Amerika Selatan (Brasil, Paraguay, Argentina)<br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong></big> Passifloraceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nMarkisa adalah tanaman merambat tropis yang dikenal dengan buahnya yang kaya rasa dan aroma khas. Tanaman ini populer sebagai bahan minuman segar, sirup, atau campuran dessert karena kandungan antioksidan dan vitaminnya yang tinggi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri Tanaman:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang:</strong> Merambat, berkayu, tumbuh cepat, dan membutuhkan penyangga atau para-para.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Berbentuk menjari dengan tiga lobus, berwarna hijau mengilap.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Bunga:</strong> Eksotis, besar, berwarna putih keunguan, mekar hanya sehari.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Buah:</strong> Bulat lonjong, kulit keras berwarna ungu tua atau kuning, daging buah berair, berbiji banyak, dan rasanya manis-asam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dikonsumsi langsung atau dijadikan jus, sirup, dan selai.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kaya vitamin A, C, dan serat pangan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bersifat antioksidan dan dipercaya membantu relaksasi serta tidur nyenyak.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Butuh sinar matahari penuh dan iklim hangat.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cocok ditanam di tanah subur dan gembur.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Perlu pemangkasan dan pemupukan rutin agar hasil optimal.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Panen dapat dilakukan 7&ndash;9 bulan setelah tanam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong></big> Passion Fruit<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> </big><em>Passiflora edulis</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> South America (Brazil, Paraguay, Argentina)<br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong> </big>Passifloraceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>General Description:</strong></big><br />\r\nPassion fruit is a tropical climbing plant known for its unique aroma and refreshing taste. Its juicy pulp is often used in drinks, syrups, or desserts due to its high antioxidant and vitamin content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Plant Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Stem:</strong> Woody climber, fast-growing, needs support like a trellis.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Glossy green with three distinct lobes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Flower:</strong> Exotic and large, with white and purple colors; blooms last only one day.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Fruit:</strong> Oval, tough outer skin (purple or yellow), juicy pulp filled with many seeds, sweet and tangy flavor.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consumed fresh or processed into juice, syrup, jam, or desserts.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Rich in vitamins A, C, and dietary fiber.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Has antioxidant properties and may support relaxation and better sleep.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Instructions:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Requires full sunlight and warm climate.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Grows best in fertile, well-drained soil.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Regular pruning and fertilizing improve fruit quality.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Harvest begins around 7&ndash;9 months after planting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Buah', '684d090187372.jpg', '684d09018b0a5.png'),
(19, 'Guava', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong> </big>Jambu Air<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong> </big><em>Syzygium aqueum</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong> </big>Asia Tenggara (Malaysia, Indonesia)<br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong> </big>Myrtaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nJambu air adalah tanaman buah tropis yang populer di pekarangan rumah maupun kebun karena buahnya yang segar, berair, dan rendah kalori. Tanaman ini memiliki nilai ekonomi tinggi dan cocok untuk ditanam di daerah dataran rendah hingga menengah.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri Tanaman:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang:</strong> Berkayu, bercabang banyak, dan dapat tumbuh setinggi 3&ndash;10 meter.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Lonjong lebar, hijau tua, dengan permukaan mengilap dan beraroma khas saat diremas.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Bunga:</strong> Kecil, putih atau kekuningan, tumbuh berkelompok di ujung ranting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Buah:</strong> Berbentuk lonceng atau kerucut, berwarna merah, hijau, atau putih, rasanya manis dan berair, dengan daging buah renyah.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dikonsumsi langsung atau dijadikan rujak, asinan, dan manisan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kaya vitamin C, serat, dan antioksidan alami.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membantu menjaga hidrasi tubuh dan sistem pencernaan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dapat tumbuh di tanah biasa, tetapi optimal di tanah subur dan cukup air.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tahan terhadap musim kering, tetapi tetap perlu penyiraman rutin.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dapat diperbanyak dengan biji atau cangkok.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Buah mulai bisa dipanen sekitar 3&ndash;5 tahun setelah tanam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong> </big>Water Apple<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> </big><em>Syzygium aqueum</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong> </big>Southeast Asia (Malaysia, Indonesia)<br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong> </big>Myrtaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>General Description:</strong><br />\r\nWater apple is a tropical fruit tree well-loved for its crisp, watery, and refreshing fruit. It&#39;s commonly planted in home gardens and has significant economic value, especially in tropical lowland areas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Plant Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Trunk:</strong> Woody, highly branched, grows up to 3&ndash;10 meters tall.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Broad and glossy green, with a distinctive aroma when crushed.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Flowers:</strong> Small, white or pale yellow, growing in clusters at the tips of branches.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Fruits:</strong> Bell- or cone-shaped, red, green, or white skin, with juicy and crunchy flesh, mildly sweet flavor.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Eaten fresh or processed into fruit salads, pickles, and sweet preserves.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>High in vitamin C, fiber, and natural antioxidants.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Helps with hydration and supports digestive health.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Instructions:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thrives in ordinary soil but grows best in fertile, well-watered ground.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tolerant of dry seasons, but regular watering enhances fruit quality.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Can be propagated via seeds or grafting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fruit can be harvested within 3&ndash;5 years of planting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Buah', '684d0b28c3db4.jpg', '684d0b28c761a.png'),
(20, 'Banana', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong></big> Pisang<br />\r\n<big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Musa spp.</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Asal:</strong></big> Asia Tenggara<br />\r\n<big><strong>Famili:</strong> </big>Musaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum:</strong></big><br />\r\nPisang merupakan tanaman tropis serbaguna yang menghasilkan buah dengan kandungan energi tinggi. Pisang sangat mudah ditemukan di Indonesia dan menjadi buah pokok yang digemari oleh semua kalangan karena rasanya manis dan teksturnya lembut.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri Tanaman:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Batang semu:</strong> Tersusun dari pelepah daun, kuat dan tegak, tingginya bisa mencapai 2&ndash;7 meter.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Daun:</strong> Besar, panjang, berwarna hijau cerah, mudah sobek oleh angin.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Bunga:</strong> Muncul dari jantung pisang, terdiri dari bunga jantan dan betina.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Buah:</strong> Tersusun dalam tandan, kulitnya bisa kuning, hijau, atau merah saat matang. Daging buahnya manis, kaya karbohidrat dan serat.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dimakan segar atau diolah menjadi keripik, kolak, cake, dll.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Daun pisang digunakan sebagai pembungkus makanan tradisional.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sumber kalium, vitamin B6, dan serat yang baik untuk kesehatan jantung dan pencernaan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tumbuh optimal di tanah subur, lembap, dan berdrainase baik.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Membutuhkan sinar matahari penuh dan air cukup.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dapat diperbanyak dengan anakan (tunas).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Panen dilakukan sekitar 9&ndash;12 bulan setelah tanam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong> </big>Banana<br />\r\n<big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> </big><em>Musa spp.</em><br />\r\n<big><strong>Origin:</strong> </big>Southeast Asia<br />\r\n<big><strong>Family:</strong></big> Musaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>General Description:</strong></big><br />\r\nThe banana is a versatile tropical plant known for its energy-rich fruit. Commonly found in tropical regions like Indonesia, bananas are beloved for their sweet flavor and soft texture, and they serve as a dietary staple.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Plant Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Pseudostem:</strong> Made of tightly packed leaf sheaths, sturdy and upright, growing 2&ndash;7 meters tall.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Leaves:</strong> Large, long, bright green, easily torn by the wind.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Flowers:</strong> Develop from the banana heart, containing both male and female flowers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Fruits:</strong> Grow in clusters, with yellow, green, or red skin when ripe. The flesh is sweet, rich in carbohydrates and fiber.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Eaten fresh or processed into chips, desserts, cakes, and more.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Banana leaves are used as traditional food wrappers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A good source of potassium, vitamin B6, and fiber&mdash;supports heart and digestive health.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care Instructions:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thrives in fertile, moist, well-drained soil.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Requires full sun and adequate water.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Propagated through suckers (offshoots).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Harvested approximately 9&ndash;12 months after planting.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Buah', '684d0c9edce0a.jpg', '684d0c9ee040f.png'),
(21, 'Sweet Potato', '<p><big><strong>Nama Umum:</strong></big> Ubi, Ubi Jalar</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Nama Ilmiah:</strong></big> <em>Ipomoea batatas</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Famili:</strong> </big>Convolvulaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><big>Asal</big>:</strong> Amerika Tengah dan Selatan</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Deskripsi Umum :</strong></big> Ubi jalar adalah tanaman akar umbi yang sangat serbaguna, dikenal karena akarnya yang membengkak dan kaya nutrisi. Bagian akarnya, yang bervariasi dalam warna dari oranye, putih, ungu, hingga kuning, merupakan sumber karbohidrat kompleks, serat, vitamin, dan mineral yang sangat baik. Ubi jalar sering dianggap sebagai salah satu tanaman pangan pokok dan memiliki rasa manis alami yang membuatnya populer dalam berbagai masakan, baik manis maupun gurih.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Ciri-Ciri :</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Akar:</strong> Membengkak, berdaging, bervariasi bentuk dan warna kulit serta daging (oranye, putih, kuning, ungu).</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Batang:</strong> Menjalar atau tegak, seringkali berbulu halus.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Daun:</strong> Berbentuk hati atau berlobus, berwarna hijau atau keunguan, bisa dimakan sebagai sayuran.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Bunga:</strong> Berbentuk corong, berwarna putih hingga ungu, jarang terlihat pada budidaya.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Rasa:</strong> Manis, dengan tekstur lembut hingga sedikit berserat setelah dimasak.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Jenis Populer :</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ubi Jalar Oranye (sering disebut ubi madu atau ubi Cilembu)</li>\r\n	<li>Ubi Jalar Putih</li>\r\n	<li>Ubi Jalar Ungu</li>\r\n	<li>Ubi Jalar Kuning</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan :</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sumber karbohidrat utama, alternatif nasi atau kentang.</li>\r\n	<li>Bahan baku aneka olahan makanan (gorengan, kolak, keripik, kue, bubur).</li>\r\n	<li>Daun mudanya bisa dimakan sebagai sayuran.</li>\r\n	<li>Kaya akan beta-karoten (pada varietas oranye), vitamin C, vitamin B6, dan kalium.</li>\r\n	<li>Digunakan dalam pakan ternak.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan :</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tumbuh baik di iklim tropis dan subtropis hangat.</li>\r\n	<li>Membutuhkan sinar matahari penuh.</li>\r\n	<li>Tanah gembur, berdrainase baik, dan kaya bahan organik.</li>\r\n	<li>Toleran terhadap kekeringan, namun produksi umbi optimal dengan penyiraman teratur.</li>\r\n	<li>Panen bisa dilakukan 90&ndash;150 hari setelah tanam, tergantung varietas.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Kategori Ubi :</strong> Ubi jalar adalah tanaman sayuran umbi, dan juga tanaman musiman (karena ditanam dan dipanen dalam satu musim tanam). Meskipun rasanya manis, ia tidak dikategorikan sebagai buah. Daunnya bisa dimakan sebagai sayuran, tetapi bagian utamanya adalah akarnya.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><strong>Common Name:</strong> </big>Sweet Potato</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Scientific Name:</strong></big> Ipomoea batatas</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Family:</strong></big> Convolvulaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Origin:</strong></big> Central and South America</p>\r\n\r\n<p>General Description:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sweet potato is a highly versatile root vegetable known for its swollen, nutrient-rich roots. Its roots, which vary in color from orange, white, purple, to yellow, are an excellent source of complex carbohydrates, fiber, vitamins, and minerals. Sweet potato is often considered a staple food crop and has a natural sweet taste that makes it popular in various dishes, both sweet and savory.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Characteristics:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Roots:</strong> Swollen, fleshy, varying in shape and color of the skin and flesh (orange, white, yellow, purple).</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Stems:</strong> Trailing or erect, often slightly hairy.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Leaves:</strong> Heart-shaped or lobed, green or purplish, edible as a vegetable.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Flowers:</strong> Funnel-shaped, white to purple, rarely seen in cultivation.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Taste:</strong> Sweet, with a soft to slightly fibrous texture after cooking.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Popular Types:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Orange Sweet Potato (often referred to as honey sweet potato or Cilembu sweet potato in some contexts)</li>\r\n	<li>White Sweet Potato</li>\r\n	<li>Purple Sweet Potato</li>\r\n	<li>Yellow Sweet Potato</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Main carbohydrate source, an alternative to rice or potatoes.</li>\r\n	<li>Raw material for various processed foods (fried snacks, compotes, chips, cakes, porridges).</li>\r\n	<li>Young leaves can be eaten as a vegetable.</li>\r\n	<li>Rich in beta-carotene (in orange varieties), Vitamin C, Vitamin B6, and potassium.</li>\r\n	<li>Used in animal feed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Care:</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Grows well in warm tropical and subtropical climates.</li>\r\n	<li>Requires full sunlight.</li>\r\n	<li>Prefers fertile, loose, well-drained, and moist soil, but not waterlogged.</li>\r\n	<li>Tolerant to drought, but optimal tuber production requires regular watering.</li>\r\n	<li>Harvest can be done 90&ndash;150 days after planting, depending on the variety.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big>Category of Sweet Potato:</big>&nbsp;Sweet potato is a tuberous vegetable plant, and also a seasonal crop (as it is planted and harvested within one growing season). Although it tastes sweet, it is not categorized as a fruit. Its leaves can be eaten as a vegetable, but its main part is the root.</p>\r\n', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cabiao', NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Musiman', '684e2ea941be3.jpg', '684e2ea9b242f.png'),
(22, 'Parsley', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Tanaman Sayur', '', '684e3268b6fab.png'),
(23, 'chili', '<p>Nama Umum: Cabai Rawit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nama Ilmiah:&nbsp;<em>Capsicum frutescens</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Asal:&nbsp;Meksiko selatan hingga kawasan tropis Amerika</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Famili:&nbsp;Solanaceae</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Deskripsi Umum:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cabai rawit (<em>Capsicum frutescens</em>) adalah tanaman perdu dari famili Solanaceae (suku terung-terongan) yang buahnya sangat populer sebagai bumbu masak karena rasanya yang sangat pedas. Tanaman ini berasal dari benua Amerika dan kini dibudidayakan secara luas di seluruh dunia, terutama di Asia Tenggara. Di Indonesia, cabai rawit menjadi salah satu komoditas hortikultura terpenting dan sering digunakan sebagai pelengkap berbagai hidangan kuliner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Buah cabai rawit memiliki ciri khas tumbuh menjulang menghadap ke atas, berbeda dengan jenis cabai lain yang menggantung. Warnanya bervariasi, mulai dari hijau atau putih saat muda, dan akan berubah menjadi merah tua ketika matang. Rasa pedasnya yang kuat berasal dari senyawa <em>capsaicinoids</em> dan tingkat kepedasannya bisa mencapai 80.000&ndash;100.000 pada skala Scoville. Selain sebagai bumbu, cabai rawit juga kaya akan nutrisi, terutama vitamin A dan C.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ciri-ciri:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', NULL, 'Tanaman Sayur', '', '684e353491010.png'),
(45, 'Intaran-Mimba', '<p><big><strong>Ciri-ciri &amp; Identifikasi</strong></big><br />\r\nDaun Intaran adalah pohon berukuran sedang hingga besar yang dapat tumbuh hingga 20 meter. Kulit batangnya tebal, kasar, dan berwarna cokelat keabu-abuan. Daunnya majemuk menyirip genap dengan 8&ndash;16 helai daun kecil yang berbentuk lonjong, bergigi di tepinya, dan berwarna hijau tua. Buahnya berbentuk lonjong kecil, berkulit keras, dan berubah warna dari hijau ke cokelat saat matang.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Habitat &amp; Persebaran</strong></big><br />\r\nTanaman ini berasal dari India dan Asia Selatan, namun kini tumbuh luas di daerah tropis termasuk Indonesia. Di Bali, pohon ini sangat umum dijumpai di pinggir jalan, pekarangan rumah, dan lahan kering.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kandungan &amp; Manfaat</strong></big><br />\r\nDaun Intaran mengandung senyawa aktif seperti azadirachtin, nimbin, dan quercetin yang memiliki sifat antibakteri, antivirus, antijamur, antiinflamasi, dan insektisida alami.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Kegunaan</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pengobatan tradisional: mengatasi jerawat, eksim, luka ringan, masalah pencernaan, dan demam.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pestisida organik: daun dan bijinya digunakan untuk mengendalikan hama tanaman secara alami.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Perawatan kulit dan rambut: minyak Intaran bermanfaat untuk ketombe, kutu rambut, dan kesehatan kulit.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan &amp; Budidaya</strong></big><br />\r\nPohon ini sangat mudah tumbuh di daerah tropis dengan tanah kering hingga sedang. Perbanyakan dapat dilakukan dengan biji. Tanaman ini juga dikenal tahan terhadap kekeringan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Nilai Budaya</strong></big><br />\r\nDi Bali, daun Intaran memiliki nilai spiritual dan sering digunakan dalam upacara adat serta simbol keindahan alis dalam seni tari.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Menanam Pohon Neem dari Bijinya</strong></em></big><em><strong><big>&nbsp;</big></strong></em><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong><big>Characteristics &amp; Identification</big></strong><br />\r\nNeem is a medium to large-sized tree that can grow up to 20 meters tall. It has a thick, rough, grayish-brown bark. The compound leaves consist of 8&ndash;16 small, oval-shaped leaflets with serrated edges and dark green color. Its fruits are small, oval drupes that turn from green to brown when ripe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Habitat &amp; Distribution</strong></big><br />\r\nNative to India and South Asia, Neem now grows widely across tropical regions, including Indonesia. In Bali, the tree is commonly found along roadsides, in home gardens, and on dry land.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Compounds &amp; Benefits</strong></big><br />\r\nNeem leaves contain active compounds such as azadirachtin, nimbin, and quercetin, which have antibacterial, antiviral, antifungal, anti-inflammatory, and natural insecticidal properties.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Traditional medicine: treats acne, eczema, minor wounds, digestive issues, and fever.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Organic pesticide: leaves and seeds are used to naturally control agricultural pests.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Skin and hair care: Neem oil is beneficial for dandruff, head lice, and overall skin health.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Cultivation &amp; Care</strong></big><br />\r\nNeem is easy to grow in tropical regions with dry to moderate soil. Propagation is commonly done by seeds. This plant is also highly drought-tolerant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Cultural Value</strong></big><br />\r\nIn Bali, Neem leaves hold spiritual significance and are often used in traditional ceremonies and as a symbol of beauty in Balinese dance performances.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><big><em>Growing Neem Tree from Seeds&nbsp;</em></big>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />', 'https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mimba', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/N2QUY53LIgY?si=sB0XQuA7_GtoAsEX\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, 'Tanaman Obat', '685c160394cc3-intaran.jpg', 'qrcode-45.png'),
(46, 'Temu Agung', '<p><big><em><strong>Ciri-ciri &amp; Identifikasi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nTemu Agung adalah tumbuhan herba tahunan dari suku Zingiberaceae, dengan tinggi batang semu ~1 m. Daunnya lanset memanjang, sering muncul setelah bunga. Bunganya keluar dari rimpang berupa bongkol dengan braktea ungu kemerahan, mahkota bunga berwarna putih kekuningan. Rimpangnya tebal, berwarna krem dengan aroma khas..</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Persebaran</strong></em></big><br />\r\nAsli dari Asia Selatan (India, Sri Lanka), dan Asia Tenggara, tumbuh liar di hutan hujan tropis. Di Indonesia, sudah banyak dibudidayakan dan ditemukan di kebun rumah .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Kandungan Kimia &amp; Khasiat</strong></big></em><br />\r\nRimpang mengandung senyawa seperti zederone, voliatil oil (alfa-pinene, cineol), dan kurkuminoid. Memiliki sifat antimikroba, anti-inflamasi, anti-radang, dan antikanker .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kegunaan</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Pengobatan kulit</strong>: digunakan untuk mengobati luka, jerawat, gatal, dan eksim.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Tonik &amp; penambah nafsu makan</strong>: sering dipakai sebagai tonik setelah melahirkan.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Kosmetik</strong>: sebagai bahan jamu kecantikan dan produk wajah alami&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Perawatan &amp; Budidaya</strong></em></big><br />\r\nPhykopis hidup baik di tempat teduh, tanah gembur dan lembap. Penyemaian dilakukan lewat pemisahan rimpang. Butuh penyiraman teratur dan kelembapan tinggi .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Nilai Budaya &amp; Ekonomi</strong></big><br />\r\nTemu Agung dihargai sebagai tanaman obat tradisional dan bahan kosmetik alami. Rimpangnya diekstrak jadi minyak atsiri untuk produk kecantikan</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Bagaimana cara menanam dan menumbuhkan kunyit?</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><em><strong>Characteristics &amp; Identification</strong></em></big><br />\r\nWild turmeric is a perennial herb of the Zingiberaceae family, growing about 1 m tall. It has lance-shaped leaves and blooms emerge from underground rhizomes. Flowers grow in a cone-shaped inflorescence with reddish-purple bracts and yellowish-white petals. Its rhizome is thick, cream-colored, and aromatic</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Habitat &amp; Distribution</strong></big></em><br />\r\nNative to South Asia (India, Sri Lanka) and Southeast Asia, it grows in tropical wet forests. In Indonesia it&rsquo;s commonly cultivated and found in home gardens .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Chemical Constituents &amp; Benefits</strong></big></em><br />\r\nThe rhizomes contain compounds such as zederone, volatile oils (alpha-pinene, cineole), and curcuminoids. They exhibit antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, analgesic, and potential anticancer properties&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Uses</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Skin remedy</strong>: treats wounds, rashes, acne, and eczema.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Health tonic</strong>: used as a postpartum tonic and to stimulate appetite.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Cosmetic ingredient</strong>: incorporated in natural skincare and beauty products .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Cultivation &amp; Care</strong></big></em><br />\r\nThrives in shaded areas, loose and moist soil. Propagate by dividing rhizomes. Requires regular watering and high humidity</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Cultural &amp; Economic Value</strong></big></em><br />\r\nValued in traditional medicine and natural cosmetics. Rhizome oil is used in skincare and aroma products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>How to plant and grow turmeric?&nbsp;</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Curcuma_aromatica', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/F7Ryhblia7s?si=1XnL4Fuu1qUepHW7\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, 'Tanaman Obat', '685c1e7294fbe-temu-agung.jpg', 'qrcode-46.png'),
(47, 'Temu Tis', '<p><big><em><strong>Ciri-ciri &amp; Identifikasi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nTemu Tis merupakan herba tahunan dari suku Zingiberaceae dengan batang semu dan daun setinggi sekitar 1 m. Rimpangnya tebal, bercabang, dengan bagian dalam putih dan aroma mangga ringan, serta rasa agak pahit</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Persebaran</strong></em></big><br />\r\nAsal Asia Selatan&ndash;Tenggara, tumbuhan ini tumbuh di hutan tropis lembap. Di Indonesia sering dibudidayakan di pekarangan dan kebun rumah .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Kandungan &amp; Khasiat</strong></big></em><br />\r\nMengandung berbagai senyawa seperti curcumin, sesquiterpen (&beta;‑turmerone, zingiberene), 1,8‑cineole, dan lain‑lain . Sifatnya antimikroba, antiinflamasi, analgesik, antioksidan, hepatoprotektif, dan antikanker&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Kegunaan</strong></big></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Pengobatan tradisional</strong>: mengatasi sakit perut, diare, demam, batuk, nyeri, luka, bisul, menstruasi tidak teratur .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Insektisida alami</strong>: ekstraknya efektif menolak nyamuk dan mematikan larva.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Tonic dan kosmetik</strong>: digunakan sebagai tonik, dalam jamu, dan kosmetik alami.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Perawatan &amp; Budidaya</strong></big></em><br />\r\nButuh cahaya tidak langsung, kelembapan tinggi, tanah subur dan gembur. Perbanyakan lewat rimpang, penyiraman rutin, suhu hangat ~25 &deg;C&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Nilai Budaya &amp; Ekonomi</strong></big></em><br />\r\nRimpangnya digunakan sebagai bahan jamu, tonik, kosmetik alami, dan terlibat dalam pengobatan tradisional seperti Usadha Bali</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Bagaimana proses penanaman dan panen dari temu tis?</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><em><strong>Characteristics &amp; Identification</strong></em></big><br />\r\nZedoary is a perennial herb in the ginger family, with pseudostems and leaves about 1 m tall. Its rhizome is thick, branched, with a white interior, faint mango aroma, and slightly bitter taste&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><big><em>Habitat &amp; Distribution</em></big></strong><br />\r\nNative to South and Southeast Asia, it thrives in moist tropical forests and is commonly grown in home gardens in Indonesia .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Chemical Constituents &amp; Benefits</strong></em></big><br />\r\nRhizomes contain curcumin, sesquiterpenes (&beta;‑turmerone, zingiberene), 1,8‑cineole, and more . They exhibit antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, analgesic, antioxidant, hepatoprotective, and anticancer activities .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Uses</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Traditional medicine</strong>: for stomach pain, diarrhea, fever, cough, wounds, ulcers, menstrual disorders&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Natural insect repellent/pesticide</strong>: effective against mosquitoes and larvae.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Tonic &amp; cosmetics</strong>: used in jamu, tonics, and natural beauty products.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultivation &amp; Care</strong></em></big><br />\r\nPrefers bright, indirect light, high humidity, rich loamy soil, and warm ~25 &deg;C temperature. Propagation via rhizome division with regular watering</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultural &amp; Economic Value</strong></em></big><br />\r\nUsed in traditional medicines, tonics, natural cosmetics, and Balinese Usadha healing rituals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>What is the process of planting and harvesting ginger?</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n', 'https://fjps.springeropen.com/articles/10.1186/s43094-021-00316-1', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/phOqLalCofs?si=9mH9B5MUsmQ8axq5\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, 'Tanaman Obat', '685cd5ea6d203-temu-tiss.jpg', 'qrcode-47.png'),
(48, 'Daun Temen', '<p><big><em><strong>Ciri-ciri &amp; Identifikasi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nDaun Temen adalah tumbuhan perdu tegak setinggi 1,5&ndash;8 m, batang berkayu dan beruas dengan permukaan ungu kehijauan. Daunnya tunggal, bentuknya oval meruncing, ujung mengkilap dan tepi rata. Bunganya tersusun majemuk di ujung batang, berwarna keunguan, dan buahnya kotak lonjong berwarna ungu kecoklatan&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><big><em>Habitat &amp; Persebaran</em></big></strong><br />\r\nAsal Papua Nugini dan Polinesia, kini tersebar di Asia Tenggara, termasuk Indonesia. Umumnya tumbuh di tempat terbuka atau pekarangan sebagai pagar dan hias .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Kandungan &amp; Khasiat</strong></big></em><br />\r\nMengandung flavonoid, saponin, tanin, alkaloid, glikosida, steroid, coumarin, dan anthraquinone. Bersifat antioksidan, antiradang, analgesik, dan astringen .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kegunaan Tradisionalhttps://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8335697/</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Wasir, sembelit, dan pencernaan</strong>: air rebusan daun efektif meredakan peradangan dan memperlancar BAB <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k1krcfL-fAw&amp;utm_source=chatgpt.com\" target=\"_blank\">youtube.com+1tiktok.com+1</a>.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Plak gigi &amp; kesehatan mulut</strong>: menghambat pertumbuhan <em>Streptococcus mutans</em> .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Kulit &amp; luka</strong>: kompres atau lulur membantu mengeringkan bisul, melunakkan borok, dan melembutkan kulit .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Kolesterol &amp; tekanan darah</strong>: fitosterol membantu menurunkan kolesterol dan mendukung sirkulasi&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Anti-inflamasi luas</strong>: mengobati radang sendi, bisul, dan kondisi inflamasi lain .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Perawatan &amp; Budidaya</strong></big><br />\r\nTumbuh baik di sinar terang penuh atau teduh parsial; media gembur dan penyiraman sedang; mudah diperbanyak lewat stek batang .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Nilai Budaya</strong></em></big><br />\r\nDalam budaya Bali, daun ini dikenal sebagai &quot;Don Temen&quot; dan digunakan dalam ramuan <em>Loloh Don Temen</em> untuk atasi panas dalam, sariawan, dan sebagai lulur tradisional .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Apa Manfaat dari Daun Ungu?&nbsp;</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><em><strong>Characteristics &amp; Identification</strong></em></big><br />\r\nPurple-leaf shrub is an upright woody plant growing 1.5&ndash;8 m tall with purple-green jointed stems. Leaves are single, oval with pointed tip, glossy, smooth-edged. Flowers form clusters at branch tips, purplish in color. Fruits are elongated rectangular capsules, purple-brown .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Distribution</strong></em></big><br />\r\nNative to Papua New Guinea and Polynesia; widespread across Southeast Asia including Indonesia. Common in home gardens as ornamental and fence plant</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Chemical Constituents &amp; Benefits</strong></big><br />\r\nContains flavonoids, saponins, tannins, alkaloids, glycosides, steroids, coumarins, and anthraquinones. Exhibits antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, analgesic, and astringent properties .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Traditional Uses</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Hemorrhoids, constipation &amp; digestion</strong>: leaf decoction reduces inflammation and supports bowel movement .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Oral health</strong>: inhibits <em>Streptococcus mutans</em>, preventing plaque .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Skin &amp; wound care</strong>: poultices or exfoliants help dry boils, soften sores, and smooth skin .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Cholesterol &amp; blood pressure</strong>: phytosterols help lower cholesterol and improve circulation .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Broad anti-inflammatory</strong>: treats arthritis, ulcers and other inflammation .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Cultivation &amp; Care</strong></big><br />\r\nThrives in full sun to partial shade; prefers loamy soil and moderate watering; easily propagated via stem cuttings .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><strong>Cultural Value</strong></big><br />\r\nKnown as &ldquo;Don Temen&rdquo; in Bali, used in <em>Loloh Don Temen</em> drink for internal heat, mouth ulcers, and as a traditional skin scrub .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong><big>What are the Penefits of Purple Leaves?&nbsp;</big></strong></em><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n', 'https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8335697/', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ynnsWZ_nOng?si=Ee6ZsPX4WGSS0Dvc\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, 'Tanaman Obat', '685ce72594e7f-daun-temen.jpg', 'qrcode-48.png'),
(49, 'Jarak Cina ', '<p><big><em><strong>Ciri-ciri &amp; Identifikasi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nJarak Cina adalah tumbuhan semak atau pohon kecil berkayu yang dapat tumbuh hingga 1&ndash;7 meter. Batangnya silindris dan mengeluarkan getah putih jika terluka. Daunnya tunggal dengan 3&ndash;9 lekukan, berwarna hijau cerah, permukaannya halus. Bunganya majemuk berwarna kuning kehijauan. Buahnya berbentuk kapsul kotak berukuran sekitar 2&ndash;4 cm berisi biji berwarna cokelat tua hingga kehitaman.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Persebaran</strong></em></big><br />\r\nTanaman ini berasal dari Amerika Tengah dan Meksiko, namun kini tumbuh luas di daerah tropis, termasuk Indonesia. Sering dijumpai di tanah kurang subur, lahan tandus, sebagai tanaman pagar atau pelindung.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kandungan &amp; Khasiat</strong></em></big><br />\r\nDaun, batang, dan bijinya mengandung senyawa saponin, flavonoid, tanin, alkaloid, glikosida, steroid, terpenoid, polifenol, dan antrakuinon. Getahnya juga kaya akan senyawa antibakteri dan antiinflamasi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kegunaan Tradisional</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pengobatan kulit dan luka: getah atau daun yang ditumbuk digunakan untuk mengobati bisul, panu, luka, dan infeksi kulit.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pencernaan: air rebusan daun digunakan sebagai pencahar alami.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Antibakteri mulut: mencegah pertumbuhan bakteri penyebab plak dan infeksi.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Anti-inflamasi: membantu meredakan nyeri sendi, rematik, dan radang.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pengusir nyamuk: ekstrak daunnya dapat membunuh larva nyamuk.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Perawatan &amp; Budidaya</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tanaman ini tahan kekeringan dan tumbuh baik di tanah kurang subur. Dapat diperbanyak dengan biji atau stek batang. Tidak memerlukan banyak pupuk dan perawatan intensif.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Nilai Budaya &amp; Ekonomi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nJarak Cina sering dimanfaatkan sebagai pagar hidup, sumber minyak nabati (biodiesel), serta bahan ramuan tradisional. Di Bali, ekstrak daun digunakan dalam pengobatan Usadha untuk berbagai penyakit kulit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Bagaimana cara perawatan Jatropha Plant?</strong></em></big>&nbsp;<strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><em><strong>Characteristics &amp; Identification</strong></em></big><br />\r\nJatropha is a woody shrub or small tree growing up to 1&ndash;7 meters tall. Its cylindrical stems exude white milky latex when injured. The leaves are simple with 3&ndash;9 lobes, bright green, and smooth. Flowers appear in clusters and are yellowish-green. The fruits are box-shaped capsules (about 2&ndash;4 cm) containing dark brown to black seeds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Distribution</strong></em></big><br />\r\nNative to Central America and Mexico, this plant is now widespread in tropical regions, including Indonesia. It grows well in poor soils, barren lands, and is often planted as hedgerows or shelterbelts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Chemical Constituents &amp; Benefits</strong></em></big><br />\r\nThe leaves, stems, and seeds contain saponins, flavonoids, tannins, alkaloids, glycosides, steroids, terpenoids, polyphenols, and anthraquinones. The latex is rich in antibacterial and anti-inflammatory compounds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Traditional Uses</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Skin and wound care: latex or crushed leaves applied to boils, ringworm, wounds, and skin infections.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Digestion: leaf decoction used as a natural laxative.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Oral health: helps prevent bacterial growth causing plaque and infections.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Anti-inflammatory: reduces joint pain, rheumatism, and inflammation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mosquito repellent: leaf extract effective against mosquito larvae.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultivation &amp; Care</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Highly drought-tolerant, thrives in poor soils. Easily propagated through seeds or stem cuttings. Requires minimal fertilizer and maintenance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultural &amp; Economic Value</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commonly used as living fences, biofuel (biodiesel) source, and in traditional medicine. In Bali, leaf extract is incorporated into <em>Usadha</em> healing practices for skin ailments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>How to care for the Jatropha Plant?</strong></em></big>&nbsp;<strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n', 'https://www.alodokter.com/7-manfaat-daun-jarak-baik-untuk-pencernaan-dan-kulit', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/mK0ZtCvxiag?si=CtscXbAtWuOz3E9w\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, 'Tanaman Obat', '685ced7089108-jarak-cina.jpg', 'qrcode-49.png'),
(50, 'Bidara ', '<p><big><em><strong>Ciri-ciri &amp; Identifikasi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nBidara adalah pohon atau semak berduri, menjulang 3&ndash;15 m, dengan batang berwarna abu-abu kehitaman dan mahkota menyebar. Daunnya sederhana, berbentuk oval, mengkilap hijau gelap di atas dan berbulu di bawah. Bunganya kecil, berwarna kuning kehijauan, tumbuh di ketiak daun. Buahnya berupa drupa oval, berukuran 2,5&ndash;6 cm, awalnya hijau lalu berubah menjadi kuning, oranye, atau merah kecokelatan saat matang&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Persebaran</strong></em></big><br />\r\nAsli dari Asia Selatan dan Asia Tenggara, kini alami tersebar luas di wilayah tropis, termasuk Indonesia. Tanaman ini toleran terhadap iklim panas dan kering, serta sering ditanam sebagai pagar hidup atau cemara pelindung .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kandungan &amp; Khasiat</strong></em></big><br />\r\nMengandung saponin, flavonoid, tanin, alkaloid, glycosida, steroid, terpenoid, polifenol, dan anthraquinone. Buah dan daun kaya vitamin C, antioksidan serta bahan bioaktif lain yang bersifat antibakteri, antiinflamasi, analgesik, dan hepatoprotektif .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kegunaan Tradisional</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Buah segar atau kering</strong>: dimakan langsung atau diolah jadi manisan, sirup, selai, hingga minuman fermentasi .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Pengobatan tradisional</strong>: biji berkhasiat sedatif, antinyeri, dan meredakan mual atau muntah&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Pakan ternak</strong>: daun dan buah digunakan sebagai pakan kambing, sapi, unggas&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Perawatan &amp; Budidaya</strong></em></big><br />\r\nTahan panas/dingin, tumbuh optimal di tanah kering hingga semi-kering, curah hujan rendah hingga sedang. Perbanyakan dengan biji atau okulasi/grafting, panen buah bisa dimulai dalam 2&ndash;4 tahun .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Nilai Budaya &amp; Ekonomi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nDi Asia Selatan, terkenal sebagai &ldquo;poor man&rsquo;s apple&rdquo; atau &ldquo;king of arid-zone fruits&rdquo; karena mudah tumbuh dan bergizi tinggi.&nbsp;Selain itu, kayunya dipakai untuk perabot, konstruksi ringan, arang, serta pagar hidup atau penahan angin</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Apa manfaat tanam&nbsp;Ziziphus mauritiana?&nbsp;</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><em><strong>Characteristics &amp; Identification</strong></em></big><br />\r\nIndian jujube is a thorny shrub or tree growing 3&ndash;15 m tall with a spreading crown. Leaves are simple, oval, glossy dark green above and hairy beneath. Flowers are small, yellowish-green, and borne in leaf axils. Fruits are drupes measuring 2.5&ndash;6 cm, turning from green to yellow, orange, or reddish-brown when ripe .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Distribution</strong></em></big><br />\r\nNative to South and Southeast Asia, now naturalized across tropical regions, including Indonesia. It tolerates hot, dry climates and is commonly used for hedges or windbreaks&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Chemical Constituents &amp; Benefits</strong></em></big><br />\r\nContains saponins, flavonoids, tannins, alkaloids, glycosides, steroids, terpenoids, polyphenols, and anthraquinones. Rich in vitamin C and antioxidants; exhibits antibacterial, anti-inflammatory, analgesic, and hepatoprotective effects .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Traditional Uses</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Fruit</strong> eaten fresh or dried, used in candies, syrups, jams, beverages&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Medicinal</strong>: seed kernels have sedative and anti-nausea properties&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Animal feed</strong>: leaves and fruit serve as nutritious fodder for livestock&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultivation &amp; Care</strong></em></big><br />\r\nDrought and heat tolerant; thrives on low-fertility soils with low to moderate rainfall. Propagation is by seed or grafting; fruiting begins within 2&ndash;4 years .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultural &amp; Economic Value</strong></em></big><br />\r\nKnown as the &ldquo;poor man&rsquo;s apple&rdquo; or &ldquo;king of arid-zone fruits&rdquo; in South Asia due to its robustness and high nutritional value. Wood is used for light construction, tools, charcoal, and as living fences/windbreaks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>What are the benefits of planting Ziziphus mauritiana?&nbsp;</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n', 'https://specialtyproduce.com/produce/Bidara_Jujube_23454.php', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/v5QRG0pqD7Y?si=yyz2S-s8yavB4gAY\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, 'Tanaman Obat', '685cf2ae696c8-bidara.jpg', 'qrcode-50.png');
INSERT INTO `tanaman` (`id`, `nama`, `deskripsi`, `nama_latin`, `famili`, `asal`, `manfaat`, `cara_menanam`, `deskripsi_en`, `link_referensi`, `video_youtube`, `link_deskripsi_en`, `kategori`, `gambar`, `qrcode`) VALUES
(51, 'Kemenyan', '<p><big><em><strong>Ciri‑ciri &amp; Identifikasi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nPohon kemenyan berukuran kecil hingga sedang, tinggi 2&ndash;8 m, dengan batang bersisik dan kulit yang mudah mengelupas. Daunnya majemuk dengan beberapa anak daun. Bunganya kecil, berwarna putih-kuning, dan buahnya berupa kapsul kecil seukuran ~1 cm&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Persebaran</strong></em></big><br />\r\nTumbuh di daerah kering dan berbatu, seperti di Oman, Yaman, Somalia, dan bagian Afrika serta Arab lainnya, hingga ketinggian &asymp;1.200 m</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kandungan &amp; Khasiat</strong></em></big><br />\r\nResinnya mengandung boswellic acids (asam boswelat), resin, dan aromatik seperti &alpha;-pinene. Terkenal karena sifat antiinflamasi, antikanker, antimikroba, dan hepatoprotektif&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kegunaan Tradisional</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Wewangian dan dupa dalam ritual agama &amp; upacara.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Aromaterapi: membantu relaksasi, melegakan pernapasan, dan mengurangi stres.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pengobatan tradisional: mengurangi peradangan akibat arthritis, meningkatkan kesehatan pencernaan dan pernapasan, serta mendukung kesehatan kulit&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Perawatan &amp; Budidaya</strong></em></big><br />\r\nPohon ini tahan kering, tumbuh di tanah berkapur serta kondisi ekstrem. Getah (resin) dipanen melalui irisan pada batang, lalu dikeringkan menjadi kemenyan</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Nilai Budaya &amp; Ekonomi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nKemenyan telah diperdagangkan sejak ribuan tahun lalu dan memiliki nilai tinggi dalam industri dupa, kosmetik, dan medis, serta dianggap suci dalam banyak budaya</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Apa manfaat dari tanaman Kemenyan?&nbsp;</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><em><strong>Characteristics &amp; Identification</strong></em></big><br />\r\nFrankincense trees are small to medium-sized (2&ndash;8 m), with papery bark that peels easily. Leaves are compound, flowers are small and yellowish-white, and fruits are ~1 cm capsules.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Distribution</strong></em></big><br />\r\nNative to arid, rocky regions in Oman, Yemen, Somalia, and parts of North Africa and Arabia, up to about 1,200 m elevation</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Chemical Constituents &amp; Benefits</strong></big></em><br />\r\nResin contains boswellic acids, resin gum, and aromatic compounds such as &alpha;-pinene. Known for anti-inflammatory, anticancer, antimicrobial, and hepatoprotective properties&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Traditional Uses</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Burned as incense in religious and ceremonial rituals.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Used in aromatherapy for relaxation, easing breathing, and stress relief.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Traditional medicine uses include treating arthritis, respiratory and digestive health issues, and skin care&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><em><big><strong>Cultivation &amp; Harvesting</strong></big></em><br />\r\nExtremely drought-tolerant, grows in calcareous, rocky soils. Resin is harvested by tapping the bark and allowing the sap to harden into tears</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultural &amp; Economic Value</strong></em></big><br />\r\nFrankincense has been traded for millennia, valued for incense, cosmetics, and medicinal uses, and holds sacred status in many cultures .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>What are the benefits of frankincense plants?&nbsp;</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/frankincense', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/SR05mDJEc1I?si=w21WK37ZbnWYjaaI\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, 'Tanaman Upacara', '685cf6b06e821-kemenyan.jpg', 'qrcode-51.png'),
(52, 'Kayu Ancak', '<p><big><em><strong>Ciri‑ciri &amp; Identifikasi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nKayu Ancak adalah pepohonan peluruh yang dapat tumbuh hingga tinggi 20 m, tapi umum ditemui sebagai pohon kecil. Batangnya berkayu, kulit abu-abu keputihan, dan mengeluarkan getah putih saat terluka. Daunnya berbentuk bulat telur dengan ujung runcing, berwarna merah saat muda dan hijau tua saat dewasa. Buahnya adalah ara kecil berwarna hitam yang manis dan disukai burung serta kelelawar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Persebaran</strong></em></big><br />\r\nTanaman ini asli dari India, Cina Selatan, Indochina, dan Malesia, termasuk Indonesia. Biasanya tumbuh liar di sepanjang sungai, tembok, dan tebing. Bisa juga menjadi epifit pada batang pohon lain.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kandungan &amp; Khasiat</strong></em></big><br />\r\nMeski belum banyak dieksplorasi secara ilmiah, Namun F. rumphii dikenal sebagai pohon pelindung, mengurangi erosi, dan populer sebagai tanaman hias atau bonsai&nbsp;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kegunaan Tradisional</strong></em></big><br />\r\nBerguna sebagai pohon peneduh di tempat ibadah dan publik. Tanaman ini juga populer sebagai bonsai, dan buahnya dapat dimakan rupa-aranya sebagai camilan atau pakan unggas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Perawatan &amp; Budidaya</strong></em></big><br />\r\nMudah tumbuh di berbagai kondisi tanah, baik dari biji, stek, maupun cangkok. Tahan kekeringan dan serbaguna sebagai tanaman hias &amp; peneduh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Nilai Budaya &amp; Ekonomi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nDi Bali dan Jawa, dimaknai religius sebagai pohon suci mirip Bodhi. Akar dan kanopi yang rindang membuatnya berperan dalam pelestarian air dan ritus adat&nbsp;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Apa ciri khas tanaman kayu ancak?&nbsp;</strong></em></big>&nbsp;<strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><em><strong>Characteristics &amp; Identification</strong></em></big><br />\r\nJava fig is a deciduous tree reaching up to 20 m, though often smaller. It has woody, pale-gray bark and exudes white latex when injured. Its leaves are ovate with pointed tips&mdash;reddish when young and dark green at maturity. The fruits are small sweet figs, dark purple-black, favored by birds and bats&nbsp;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Distribution</strong></em></big><br />\r\nNative to India, southern China, Indochina, and Malaysia, including Indonesia. Commonly found growing wild along rivers, walls, cliffs, and as epiphytes on other trees&nbsp;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Constituents &amp; Uses</strong></em></big><br />\r\nThough not fully studied, it is known as a shade and erosion control tree, also widely used in bonsai cultivation&nbsp;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Traditional Uses</strong></em></big><br />\r\nUtilized as shade tree in public spaces and sacred sites, popular for bonsai. Its figs are edible as snacks or bird feed&nbsp;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultivation &amp; Care</strong></em></big><br />\r\nGrows easily from seed, cuttings, or air-layering; tolerant of dry soils; commonly used as ornamental and shade trees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultural &amp; Economic Value</strong></em></big><br />\r\nViewed as a sacred tree in Bali and Java, akin to the Bodhi tree. Its canopy and roots support water conservation and religious rituals&nbsp;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>What are the characteristics of the wood that are used in the tree?&nbsp;</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ficus_rumphii', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/OY6IyKbMCDQ?si=4od5L3sMojFySsOp\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, 'Tanaman Upacara', '685cfa13c4d5a-ancak.jpg', 'qrcode-52.png'),
(53, 'Walisongo', '<p><big><em><strong>Ciri-ciri &amp; Identifikasi</strong></em></big><br />\r\nWalisongo adalah pohon atau perdu selalu hijau, tumbuh tinggi antara 5&ndash;10 m. Batangnya tunggal dan bercabang, dengan daun majemuk menjuntai: umumnya 9&ndash;12 helai panjang, menyerupai payung. permukaan daun mengkilap hijau tua&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Persebaran</strong></em></big><br />\r\nAsli dari hutan hujan tropis di Australia (Queensland, Northern Territory), Papua, dan Jawa. Kini juga populer sebagai tanaman hias di berbagai wilayah tropis dan subtropis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kandungan &amp; Khasiat</strong></em></big><br />\r\nDaunnya mengandung flavonoid dan terpenoid&mdash;senyawa yang sering dikaitkan dengan aktivitas antioksidan, antiinflamasi, dan detoksifikasi darah.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Kegunaan Tradisional</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sulit ditemukan penggunaan obat tradisional yang luas, namun tanaman ini dipercaya dapat menenangkan dan sebagai dekorasi spiritual.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dipercaya membawa keberuntungan saat memiliki 9 helai daun per tangkai&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Banyak diletakkan di ruangan publik sebagai peneduh dan penyaring udara .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Perawatan &amp; Budidaya</strong></em></big><br />\r\nTanaman ini mudah dirawat: membutuhkan cahaya terang tidak langsung, kelembapan sedang, dan penyiraman ketika permukaan tanah mulai kering. Tahan terhadap panas dan cuaca tropis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Nilai Budaya &amp; Mitos</strong></em></big><br />\r\nSering dikaitkan dengan Wali Songo karena jumlah daun&mdash;ada kepercayaan bahwa jika jumlah daun per tangkai sembilan, tanaman membawa keberuntungan dan pelindung spiritual dari roh halus</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Bagaimana cara merawat tanaman walisongo?&nbsp;</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong></p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><big><em><strong>Characteristics &amp; Identification</strong></em></big><br />\r\nThe umbrella tree is an evergreen tree/shrub, growing 5&ndash;10 m tall. It has a main stem that branches, bearing glossy pinnate leaves with 9&ndash;12 leaflets arranged like an umbrella.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Habitat &amp; Distribution</strong></em></big><br />\r\nNative to tropical rainforests in Australia (Queensland, Northern Territory), Papua, and Java. Now widely cultivated as an ornamental plant in tropical and subtropical regions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Chemical Constituents &amp; Benefits</strong></em></big><br />\r\nLeaves contain flavonoids and terpenoids, which are known for antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and blood-detoxifying effects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Traditional &amp; Cultural Uses</strong></em></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Though not widely used medicinally, it&#39;s valued for its relaxing presence and spiritual symbolism.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Believed to bring good fortune when bearing nine leaflets per stem.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Used as an indoor/outdoor ornamental for shade and air purification .</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultivation &amp; Care</strong></em></big><br />\r\nEasy to care for; prefers bright, indirect light, moderate humidity, and watering when soil surface is dry. Tolerant of heat and tropical conditions .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>Cultural Significance &amp; Myths</strong></em></big><br />\r\nAssociated with the nine Walisongo saints because of its nine-leaflet pattern; believed to bring luck and protection from spirits</p>\r\n\r\n<p><big><em><strong>How to take care of walisongo plants?&nbsp;</strong></em></big><strong>[YOUTUBE_VIDEO]</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'https://www.orami.co.id/magazine/tanaman-walisongo', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/0AddZH5KZRo?si=vmzBgetP1LhBCj1M\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, 'Tanaman Upacara', '685cfd565eb79-walisongo.jpg', 'qrcode-53.png');

